---
description: Replyline core workflow and safety baseline
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Work directly on `main`; do not open PRs in routine solo flow.
- Before edits, run `git status --short --branch` and `git rev-parse HEAD`.
- Keep changes minimal and task-scoped; avoid unrelated refactors.
- Never weaken or remove tests to force green checks.
- Never claim checks passed unless commands were actually run.
- Never log secrets or raw sensitive transcript/prompt/provider payload data.
- For behavior changes, run `pnpm verify:fast`.
- If JS deps changed, also run `pnpm audit:npm`.
- If Rust deps changed, also run `pnpm rust:deps`.
- Final summary must include changed files, validation matrix, residual risks, and next recommended block.